 TV Host\n| [[Nick Cannon]]\n| {{pending}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[MTV Movie & TV Awards]]\n| [[2019 MTV Movie & TV Awards|2019]]\n| Best Host\n| Nick Cannon\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|last=Bell|first=Crystal|title=2019 MTV Movie & TV Awards Winners: See the Full List|url=https://www.mtv.ca/mtv-movie-and-tv-awards-winners/|website=[[MTV]]|date=June 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620221134/https://www.mtv.ca/mtv-movie-and-tv-awards-winners/|archive-date=June 20, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[People's Choice Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[45th People's Choice Awards|2019]]\n| The Competition Show of 2019\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=Here Are All the 2019 E! People's Choice Awards Winners|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8543205/2019-peoples-choice-awards-winners|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=November 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402041818/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8543205/2019-peoples-choice-awards-winners|archive-date=April 2, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n| The Competition Contestant of 2019\n| [[T-Pain]]\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Producers Guild of America Award|Producers Guild of America Awards]]\n| [[31st Producers Guild of America Awards|2020]]\n| Outstanding Producer of Game & Competition Television \n| Craig Plestis, Izzie Pick Ibarra, Nikki Varhely-Gillingham, Rosie Seitchik, Stacey Thomas-Muir, Nick Cannon, Ashley Sylvester, Lindsay Tuggle, Pete Cooksley, Chelsea Candelaria, Anne Chanthavong, Zo\u00eb Ritchken, Deena Katz, Erin Brady, Jeff Kmiotek, Lexi Shoemaker\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=2020 PGA Awards Winners|url=https://www.producersguild.org/page/2020award_winners|website=[[Producers Guild of America]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307135545/https://www.producersguild.org/page/2020award_winners|archive-date=March 7, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Brunico Communications|Realscreen Awards]]\n| 2020\n| Talent & Studio-Based Competition\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{won}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=2020 Winners & Nominees|url=https://awards.realscreen.com/Winners/Winner/2020|website=Realscreen|publisher=[[Brunico Communications]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200405233615/https://awards.realscreen.com/Winners/Winner/2020|archive-date=April 5, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Shorty Awards]]\n| [[11th Shorty Awards|2019]]\n| Best in Entertainment Sites & Apps \n| ''The Masked Singer'' Social Hub\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=Best in Entertainment Sites & Apps|url=https://shortyawards.com/category/11th/entertainment-apps|website=[[Shorty Awards]]|date=January 28, 2019|archive-url=http://archive.today/poEjN|archive-date=April 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[2019 Teen Choice Awards|2019]]\n| Choice Reality TV Show\n| ''The Masked Singer''\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=text-align:center;\"| <ref>{{cite web|title=Here Are All the Winners From the 2019 Teen Choice Awards|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8527134/teen-choice-awards-2019-winners-list|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=August 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200215073036/https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/awards/8527134/teen-choice-awards-2019-winners-list|archive-date=February 15, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Spin-offs==\n===''The Masked Singer: After the Mask''===\n[[File:Masked-singer-after-the-mask.png|upright|thumb|Logo for the aftershow]]\nOn April 8, 2020, Fox announced that Nick Cannon will host an [[aftershow]] of the series titled ''The Masked Singer: After the Mask'' on Wednesdays at 9:00 p.m. for four weeks starting on April 22. He will host the show from his house and discuss the outcome of the preceding episode with celebrity guests appearing remotely.<ref>{{cite web|last=Schneider|first=Michael|title=''The Masked Singer'' After-Show, Hosted by Nick Cannon, to Launch on Fox|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/the-masked-singer-after-the-mask-nick-cannon-fox-1234574761/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=April 8, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Roots|first=Kimberly|title=''The Masked Singer'' to Get Aftershow|url=https://tvline.com/2020/04/08/the-masked-singer-aftershow-nick-cannon-season-3-fox/|website=[[TVLine]]|date=April 8, 2020}}</ref> In the second episode, Gordon Ramsay is set to appear alongside the panelists, with the masked competitors bringing a \"signature dish\" to them that acts as a clue to their indentity.<ref name=\"VAR Mar 26\"/>\n\n===''The Masked Dancer''===\nOn January 7, 2020, at the winter [[Television Critics Association]] press tour, Fox Alternative Entertainment and [[Warner Bros. Television]] announced that they had ordered a spin-off series, ''The Masked Dancer'', with [[Ellen DeGeneres]] as executive producer. DeGeneres had previously conducted ''The Masked Dancer'' as a recurring segment of her syndicated [[talk show]] ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', as a self-admitted parody of ''The Masked Singer''. DeGeneres stated that the show was \"gonna be just as fun and suspenseful\", but \"with a lot more [[krumping]].\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/01/the-masked-dancer-fox-partners-with-ellen-degeneres-on-the-masked-singer-spin-off-1202823169/|title=''The Masked Dancer'': Fox Partners With Ellen DeGeneres On ''The Masked Singer'' Spinoff \u2013 TCA|last=White|first=Peter|date=January 7, 2020|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/pug-almost-passes-out-playing-ellen-degeneres-latest-masked-singer-ripoff-video/|title=A Pug Almost Passes Out Playing Ellen DeGeneres' Latest ''Masked Dancer''|date=February 18, 2019|website=[[TheWrap]]}</ref>\n\n==Other media==\nOn February 12, 2020, it was announced that the show would be getting a live national tour with shows in over forty-five cities. Beginning at the [[Fox Theatre (Detroit)|Fox Theatre]] in [[Detroit|Detroit, Michigan]] on May 28, 2020, the tour will feature two celebrity hosts as well as a local mystery celebrity who is unmasked at the end of each show.<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20200212005953/en/MASKED-SINGER-Unveils-45-City-U.S.-National|title=''The Masked Singer'' Unveils 45+ City U.S. National Tour|via=[[Business Wire]]|date=February 12, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Schneider|first=Michael|title=''The Masked Singer'' Announces Nationwide Concert Tour This Summer|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/masked-singer-concert-tour-summer-1203502739/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=February 12, 2020}}</ref> On February 24, 2020, toy manufacturer Jazwares announced they had partnered with Fox to release a ''Masked Singer''-inspired karaoke microphone under their \"First Act\" brand. The microphone will include a voice-changing feature and be sold at retail later in the year.<ref>{{Cite press release|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/jazwares-announces-new-first-act-karaoke-microphone-inspired-by-foxs-mega-hit-singing-competition-series-the-masked-singer-301009810.html|title=Jazwares Announces New First Act\u2122 Karaoke Microphone Inspired By Fox's Mega-Hit Singing Competition Series, ''The Masked Singer'' |date=February 24, 2020|publisher=Jazwares|via=[[PR Newswire]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225165959/https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/jazwares-announces-new-first-act-karaoke-microphone-inspired-by-foxs-mega-hit-singing-competition-series-the-masked-singer-301009810.html|archive-date=February 25, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.licenseglobal.com/toys-games/ny-toy-fair-jazwares-unveils-ufc-masked-singer-fortnite-and-all-elite-wrestling-toys|title=Jazwares Announces New First Act\u2122 Karaoke Microphone Inspired By Fox's Mega-Hit Singing Competition Series, ''The Masked Singer'' |date=February 24, 2020|website=License Global|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200410063545/https://www.licenseglobal.com/toys-games/ny-toy-fair-jazwares-unveils-ufc-masked-singer-fortnite-and-all-elite-wrestling-toys|archive-date=April 20, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb title}}\n\n{{sequence\n|prev=''[[The World's Best ]]''<br />[[Super Bowl LIII|2019]]\n|list=[[List of Super Bowl lead-out programs|Super Bowl lead-out program]]<br />''The Masked Singer''<br />[[Super Bowl LIV|2020]]\n|next=TBA\n}}\n\n{{The Masked Singer (American TV series)}}\n{{Masked Singer series}}\n{{FOXNetwork Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Masked Singer, The}}\n[[Category:2019 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Fox Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:2010s American music television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American game shows]]\n[[Category:2020s American music television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American game shows]]\n[[Category:American television series based on South Korean television series]]\n[[Category:Music competitions in the United States]]\n[[Category:Super Bowl lead-out programs]]\n[[Category:Television series by Endemol]]\n[[Category:Television series by Fox Entertainment]]\n", "name_user": "Heartfox", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Masked_Singer_(American_TV_series)"}
{"title_page": "Mazda Ibuki", "text_new": "{{Infobox automobile\n| image        = \n| name         = Mazda Ibuki\n| manufacturer = [[Mazda]]\n| class        = [[Concept car]]\n| body_style   = 2-door [[Roadster (automobile)|roadster]]\n| layout       = [[Front-engine, rear-wheel-drive layout#Front mid-engine, rear-wheel-drive layout|Front mid-engine, rear-wheel-drive]]\n| platform     = [[Mazda F platform#SE|Mazda SE platform]]\n| engine       = {{convert|1.6|L|cuin|abbr=on}} [[Mazda Z engine#Z6/M|''MZR ZM-DE'']] [[Overhead camshaft#Dual overhead camshaft|DOHC]] [[Inline-four engine|I4]] ([[Hybrid electric vehicle|gasoline electric]])<ref name=\"Motor1\"/>\n| transmission = 6-speed [[Manual transmission|manual]]\n| wheelbase    = {{convert|2330|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| length       = {{convert|3640|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| width        = {{convert|1720|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| height       = {{convert|1230|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| weight       = \n| related      = [[Mazda RX-8]]<br/>[[Mazda MX-5 (NC)]]\n| designer     = [[Moray Callum]]<br/>Truman Pollard<ref name=\"Car Design News\"/><br/>Isao T\u014dda<ref name=\"TopSpeed\"/>\n}}\n\nThe {{nihongo4|'''Mazda Ibuki'''|\u30de\u30c4\u30c0\u30fb\u606f\u5439|Matsuda Ibuki}} was a [[concept car]] by [[Mazda]] revealed at the 2003 [[Tokyo Motor Show]]<ref name=\"Motor1\">{{cite web |url=https://www.motor1.com/news/362684/mazda-ibuki-concept-we-forgot/ |title=2003 Mazda Ibuki: Concept We Forgot |first=Adrian |last=Padeanu |website=[[Motorsport Network]] |date=2019-07-31 |accessdate=2019-08-25}}</ref><ref name=\"Car Design News\">{{cite web |url=https://cardesignnews.com/media/imported/207775/207775.html |title=Concept Car of the Week: Mazda Ibuki (2003) |author=Dachet, Flavien |website=[[Car Design News]] |date=2014-02-21 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"AutomobileMag\">{{cite magazine |url=https://www.automobilemag.com/news/ibuki/ |title=A Closer Look: Mazda Ibuki Concept |magazine=[[Automobile (magazine)|Automobile magazine]] |date=2003-11-13 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"Roadster Blog\">{{cite web |url=http://www.roadster.blog/2013/07/ibuki-concept.html |title=Mazda Ibuki Concept |website=Roadster Blog |date=2013-07-04 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref> and the 2004 [[Chicago Auto Show]]. Although not its inspiration, the Ibuki previewed the NC MX-5 ahead of its 2005 launch.<ref name=\"TopSpeed\">{{cite web |url=https://www.topspeed.com/cars/mazda/2003-mazda-ibuki-concept-ar31762.html |title=2003 Mazda Ibuki Concept |author=Nicusor, Blas |website=TopSpeed.com |date=2007-04-09 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"Evo\">{{cite magazine |url=https://www.evo.co.uk/mazda/mx-5/18411/concept-cars-the-mazda-ibuki |title=Concept cars - the Mazda Ibuki |author=Ingram, Antony |magazine=[[Evo (magazine)|Evo magazine]] |date=2016-10-15 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"C&D\">{{cite magazine |url=https://www.caranddriver.com/news/mazda-ibuki-auto-shows |title=Mazda Ibuki |magazine=[[Car and Driver]] |date=2004-02-01 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref>\n\nThe Ibuki, which is Japanese for \"breathing new energy\" or \"adding vigor\",<ref name=\"Car Design News\"/> was built on a variation of the [[Mazda RX-8]]'s platform. Its body consisted of a reinforced open frame with a rigid backbone frame under the transmission tunnel and plastic body panels. To further emphasize its light weight, its brake discs and inner door panels were made of [[Aluminium|aluminum]], the propeller shaft and engine frame used [[Carbon fibers|carbon fiber]], and its wheels were cast in [[magnesium alloy]].<ref name=\"Car Design News\"/><ref name=\"TopSpeed\"/> Power came from a {{convert|1.6|L|cuin|abbr=on}} [[Mazda Z engine#Z6/M|MZR ZM-DE]] [[Inline-four engine|I4]] engine paired with an electric motor and mated to a 6-speed [[manual transmission]], generating {{convert|180|bhp|kW|abbr=on}} and {{convert|133|lbf.ft|Nm|abbr=on}} torque.<ref name=\"Motor1\"/><ref name=\"Car Design News\"/><ref name=\"Roadster Blog\"/><ref name=\"Auto123\">{{cite web |url=https://www.auto123.com/en/car-reviews/2003-mazda-ibuki-concept/28641/ |title=2003 Mazda Ibuki Concept |website=Auto123.com |access-date=2018-10-08}}</ref> To ensure an even weight distribution, the [[air conditioning]] unit was mounted behind the seats. Safety features included a four-point active rollbar in the front pillars and rear cowl section that instantly lifted up under impact sensor control in case of a rollover.<ref name=\"Car Design News\"/><ref name=\"TopSpeed\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://insidemazda.mazdausa.com/vehicle-page/ibuki/}}\n\n{{Mazda MX-5}}\n{{Mazda vehicles}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mazda Ibuki}}\n[[Category:Mazda concept vehicles|Ibuki]]\n[[Category:Mazda MX-5]]\n[[Category:Sports cars]]\n[[Category:Retro-style automobiles]]\n[[Category:Roadsters]]\n[[Category:Front mid-engine, rear-wheel-drive vehicles]]\n[[Category:Hybrid electric cars]]\n\n\n{{Modern-auto-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox automobile\n| image        = \n| name         = Mazda Ibuki\n| manufacturer = [[Mazda]]\n| class        = [[Concept car]]\n| body_style   = 2-door [[Roadster (automobile)|roadster]]\n| layout       = [[Front-engine, rear-wheel-drive layout#Front mid-engine, rear-wheel-drive layout|Front mid-engine, rear-wheel-drive]]\n| platform     = [[Mazda F platform#SE|Mazda SE platform]]\n| engine       = {{convert|1.6|L|cuin|abbr=on}} [[Mazda Z engine#Z6/M|''MZR ZM-DE'']] [[Overhead camshaft#Dual overhead camshaft|DOHC]] [[Inline-four engine|I4]] ([[Hybrid electric vehicle|gasoline electric]])<ref name=\"Motor1\"/>\n| transmission = 6-speed [[Manual transmission|manual]]\n| wheelbase    = {{convert|2330|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| length       = {{convert|3640|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| width        = {{convert|1720|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| height       = {{convert|1230|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| weight       = \n| related      = [[Mazda RX-8]]<br/>[[Mazda MX-5 (NC)]]\n| designer     = [[Moray Callum]]<br/>Truman Pollard<ref name=\"Car Design News\"/><br/>Isao T\u014dda<ref name=\"TopSpeed\"/>\n}}\n\nThe {{nihongo4|'''Mazda Ibuki'''|\u30de\u30c4\u30c0\u30fb\u606f\u5439|Matsuda Ibuki}} was a [[concept car]] by [[Mazda]] revealed at the 2003 [[Tokyo Motor Show]]<ref name=\"Motor1\">{{cite web |url=https://www.motor1.com/news/362684/mazda-ibuki-concept-we-forgot/ |title=2003 Mazda Ibuki: Concept We Forgot |first=Adrian |last=Padeanu |website=[[Motorsport Network]] |date=2019-07-31 |accessdate=2019-08-25}}</ref><ref name=\"Car Design News\">{{cite web |url=https://cardesignnews.com/media/imported/207775/207775.html |title=Concept Car of the Week: Mazda Ibuki (2003) |author=Dachet, Flavien |website=[[Car Design News]] |date=2014-02-21 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"AutomobileMag\">{{cite magazine |url=https://www.automobilemag.com/news/ibuki/ |title=A Closer Look: Mazda Ibuki Concept |magazine=[[Automobile (magazine)|Automobile magazine]] |date=2003-11-13 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"Roadster Blog\">{{cite web |url=http://www.roadster.blog/2013/07/ibuki-concept.html |title=Mazda Ibuki Concept |website=Roadster Blog |date=2013-07-04 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref> and the 2004 [[Chicago Auto Show]].<ref name=\"TopSpeed\">{{cite web |url=https://www.topspeed.com/cars/mazda/2003-mazda-ibuki-concept-ar31762.html |title=2003 Mazda Ibuki Concept |author=Nicusor, Blas |website=TopSpeed.com |date=2007-04-09 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"Evo\">{{cite magazine |url=https://www.evo.co.uk/mazda/mx-5/18411/concept-cars-the-mazda-ibuki |title=Concept cars - the Mazda Ibuki |author=Ingram, Antony |magazine=[[Evo (magazine)|Evo magazine]] |date=2016-10-15 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref><ref name=\"C&D\">{{cite magazine |url=https://www.caranddriver.com/news/mazda-ibuki-auto-shows |title=Mazda Ibuki |magazine=[[Car and Driver]] |date=2004-02-01 |access-date=2018-10-02}}</ref> It became the design basis for the third generation [[Mazda MX-5 (NC)]].<ref name=\"Motor1\"/><ref name=\"Evo\"/>\n\nThe Ibuki, which is Japanese for \"breathing new energy\" or \"adding vigor\",<ref name=\"Car Design News\"/> was built on a variation of the [[Mazda RX-8]]'s platform. Its body consisted of a reinforced open frame with a rigid backbone frame under the transmission tunnel and plastic body panels. To further emphasize its light weight, its brake discs and inner door panels were made of [[Aluminium|aluminum]], the propeller shaft and engine frame used [[Carbon fibers|carbon fiber]], and its wheels were cast in [[magnesium alloy]].<ref name=\"Car Design News\"/><ref name=\"TopSpeed\"/> Power came from a {{convert|1.6|L|cuin|abbr=on}} [[Mazda Z engine#Z6/M|MZR ZM-DE]] [[Inline-four engine|I4]] engine paired with an electric motor and mated to a 6-speed [[manual transmission]], generating {{convert|180|bhp|kW|abbr=on}} and {{convert|133|lbf.ft|Nm|abbr=on}} torque.<ref name=\"Motor1\"/><ref name=\"Car Design News\"/><ref name=\"Roadster Blog\"/><ref name=\"Auto123\">{{cite web |url=https://www.auto123.com/en/car-reviews/2003-mazda-ibuki-concept/28641/ |title=2003 Mazda Ibuki Concept |website=Auto123.com |access-date=2018-10-08}}</ref> To ensure an even weight distribution, the [[air conditioning]] unit was mounted behind the seats. Safety features included a four-point active rollbar in the front pillars and rear cowl section that instantly lifted up under impact sensor control in case of a rollover.<ref name=\"Car Design News\"/><ref name=\"TopSpeed\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://insidemazda.mazdausa.com/vehicle-page/ibuki/}}\n\n{{Mazda MX-5}}\n{{Mazda vehicles}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mazda Ibuki}}\n[[Category:Mazda concept vehicles|Ibuki]]\n[[Category:Mazda MX-5]]\n[[Category:Sports cars]]\n[[Category:Retro-style automobiles]]\n[[Category:Roadsters]]\n[[Category:Front mid-engine, rear-wheel-drive vehicles]]\n[[Category:Hybrid electric cars]]\n\n\n{{Modern-auto-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Carmaker1", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mazda_Ibuki"}
{"title_page": "Jeet Prime", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox TV channel\n|name=Jeet Prime\n|logofile=Jeet_Prime's_logo.png\n|logosize=\n|logoalt=\n|logocaption=\n|launch={{start date|df=yes|2018|02|12}}\n|owner=[[Discovery Networks Asia Pacific]]\n|picture format=4:3 ([[576i]], [[SDTV]]) <br>16:9 ([[1080i]], [[HDTV]])\n|slogan=\n|former names = Discovery Jeet (2018-19)\n|headquarters= [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n|country=India\n|language=[[Hindi]]<br>[[Tamil language|Tamil]]<br>[[Telugu language|Telugu]]<br>[[English language|English]] \n|replaced names=[[Investigation Discovery]]\n|sister names=[[Animal Planet India|Animal Planet]]<br />[[TLC India|TLC]]<br />[[Discovery Turbo]]<br />[[Discovery Kids (India)|Discovery Kids]]<br />[[Discovery Science (India)|Discovery Science]]<br />[[Discovery Channel (India)|Discovery Channel]]<br />[[DSport]]\n|sat serv 1=[[Tata Sky]]\n|sat chan 1=Channel 155\n|sat serv 2=[[Videocon d2h]]\n|sat chan 2=Channel 111\n|sat serv 3=[[Airtel Digital TV]]\n|sat chan 3=Channel 135 (SD)<br>Channel 136 (HD)\n|sat serv 4=[[Dish TV]]\n|sat chan 4=Channel 126\n|cable serv 1=DEN\n|cable chan 1=Channel 106\n|cable serv 2=[[Hathway]]\n|cable chan 2=Channel 10\n|cable serv 3=GTPL\n|cable chan 3=Channel 8\n|cable serv 4=Fastway\n|cable chan 4=Channel 10\n|cable serv 5=IMCL\n|cable chan 5=Channel 141\n|cable serv 6=BRI Infotainment\n|cable chan 6=Channel 109\n|cable serv 7=BRDS\n|cable chan 7=Channel 108\n|cable serv 8=NXT Digital\n|cable chan 8=Channel 212\n|cable serv 9=SCOD18\n|cable chan 9=Channel 107\n|cable serv 10=7STAR\n|cable chan 10=Channel 6\n|cable serv 11=Homecable\n|cable chan 11=Channel 8\n|cable serv 12=JPR\n|cable chan 12=Channel 108\n|cable serv 13=[[Siti Cable]]\n|cable chan 13=Channel 110/207\n|cable serv 14=A.C.N\n|cable chan 14=Channel 15\n|cable serv 15=Radiant Digitech\n|cable chan 15=Channel 111\n|cable serv 16=ICC Pune\n|cable chan 16=Channel 73\n|cable serv 17=SR Digital\n|cable chan 17=Channel 7\n|cable serv 18=Digiana\n|cable chan 18=Channel 141\n|cable serv 19=Sangli Media Communications\n|cable chan 19=Channel 106\n|cable serv 20=ECN|cable chan 20=Channel 11}}\n\n'''Jeet Prime''' is a Hindi general entertainment channel launched by [[Discovery Networks Asia Pacific]] on 12 February 2018 which airs shows from [[Investigation Discovery (India)|Investigation Discovery]] and [[Scripps Networks Interactive|Scripps]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/people/discovery-expands-vijay-rajput-s-role-to-head-of-dsport-channel-11578558454296.html|title=Discovery expands Vijay Rajput\u2019s role to head of DSPORT channel|first=Lata|last=Jha|date=9 January 2020|website=Livemint}}</ref><ref name=Scrips/> The channel was originally launched as ''Discovery Jeet'' and initially featured original programming.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/gecs/not-relying-on-movies-to-garner-jeets-viewership-karan-bajaj-180206|title=Not relying on movies to garner Jeet's viewership: Karan Bajaj|date=2018-02-06|work=Indian Television Dot Com|access-date=2018-02-14|language=en}}</ref>\n[[File:Discovery Jeet logo.png|200px|thumb|right|Logo as Discovery Jeet]]\n\n== History ==\nThis channel replaced [[Investigation Discovery (India)|Investigation Discovery]] on 1 February 2018 and was officially launched on 12 February 2018.<ref name=\":0\" /> The company also shifted their headquarters from Delhi to Mumbai which is more suited for building a national general entertainment channel.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/p3TPPsBFpoMyl9HhgB1w4M/Karan-Bajaj-A-winning-discovery.html|title=Karan Bajaj: A winning discovery|last=Bansal|first=Shuchi|date=2017-12-22|work=Livemint|access-date=2018-02-14}}</ref> It aims to create 1000 hours of original content a year. The shows will also be available digitally via [[Netflix]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe channel had a reach of 140 million on the day of launch.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.televisionpost.com/jeet-had-a-reach-of-140-million-on-launch-day-claims-discovery/|title=Jeet had a reach of 140 million on launch day, claims Discovery|website=www.televisionpost.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-14}}</ref> Discovery Jeet is also available on Jio TV app and Airtel TV app.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indianable.com/discovery-jeet-channel-number/|title=Watch Discovery Jeet on Jio TV and Airtel TV|website=www.indianable.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-15}}</ref>\n\nDiscovery announced plans to revamp the channel with dubbed content from [[Scripps Networks Interactive|Scripps]] after low ratings.<ref name=Scrips>{{Cite web|url=http://www.afaqs.com/news/story/52900_Discovery-to-dub-foreign-content-as-Hindi-GEC-channel-doesnt-stir-viewers|title=Discovery to dub foreign content as Hindi GEC channel doesn't stir viewers|website=www.afaqs.com|language=en|access-date=2018-05-08}}</ref>\n\n==Programming==\n'''Current'''\n\nAs of October 2018, channel's new programming with Hindi dubbed content from [[Scripps Networks Interactive|Scripps]]\n\n[[Cutthroat Kitchen]]\n\n[[Toddlers & Tiaras|Toddler's and Tiaras]]\n\n[[Guilty Pleasures (TV series)|Guilty Pleasure]]\n\n[[90 Day Fianc\u00e9|90 Days Fianc\u00e9]]\n\n[[Deadly Women]]\n\n===Former===\nAs of June 2018, the channel replaced original programming with Hindi dubbed original shows of the [[Investigation Discovery (India)|Investigation Discovery]] channel.<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n* ''[[A Crime to Remember]]''\n* ''[[Cry Wolfe]]''\n* ''[[Deadly Sins (TV Series)|Deadly Sins]]''\n* ''[[Evil Kin]]''\n* ''[[Murder Among Friends (2016 TV series)|Murder Among Friends]]'' \n* ''[[Unraveled (TV series)|Unraveled]]''\n* ''[[The Perfect Murder (TV series)|The Perfect Murder]]''\n* ''[[Tabloid (TV series)|Tabloid]]''\n* ''[[Web of Lies (TV series)|Web of Lies]]''\n\n===Former original programming===\n*''[[21 Sarfarosh - Saragarhi 1897]]''<ref name=\"DiscvoveryJeet\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.televisionpost.com/discovery-jeet-to-cease-original-programming-by-june-end-launch-fresh-intl-content-in-h2-fy19/|title=Discovery Jeet to cease original programming by June-end, launch fresh intl content in H2 FY19|website=www.televisionpost.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-10}}</ref>\n*''[[Anjaan: Special Crimes Unit]]''<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n*''Comedy High School''<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n*''[[Darr Ke Uss Paar]]''<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n*''Gabru: Hip Hop Ke Shehzaade''<ref name=Postt>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/gecs/discovery-jeet-postpones-2-show-launches-to-late-march-180222|title=Discovery Jeet postpones 2 show launches to late March|date=22 February 2018|publisher=Indian Television|accessdate=25 February 2019}}</ref>\n*''Khan No.1''<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n*''Man vs Wild with Sunny Leone''<ref name=Postt/>\n*''[[Mere Papa Hero Hiralal]]'' <ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n*''Shaadi Jasoos''<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n*''[[Swami Ramdev - Ek Sangharsh]]''<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n\n== External links ==\n[https://www.facebook.com/DiscoveryJeet Official Facebook page]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}{{Discovery Communications}}\n[[Category:Television stations in Mumbai]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television stations]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television channels in India]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 2018]]\n[[Category:Discovery Networks]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2019}}\n{{Infobox TV channel\n|name=Jeet Prime\n|logofile=Jeet_Prime's_logo.png\n|logosize=\n|logoalt=\n|logocaption=\n|launch={{start date|df=yes|2018|02|12}}\n|owner=[[Discovery Networks Asia Pacific]]\n|picture format=4:3 ([[576i]], [[SDTV]]) <br>16:9 ([[1080i]], [[HDTV]])\n|slogan=\n|former names = Discovery Jeet (2018-19)\n|headquarters= [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], [[India]]\n|country=India\n|language=[[Hindi]]<br>[[Tamil language|Tamil]]<br>[[Telugu language|Telugu]]<br>[[English language|English]] \n|replaced names=[[Investigation Discovery]]\n|sister names=[[Animal Planet India|Animal Planet]]<br />[[TLC India|TLC]]<br />[[Discovery Turbo]]<br />[[Discovery Kids (India)|Discovery Kids]]<br />[[Discovery Science (India)|Discovery Science]]<br />[[Discovery Channel (India)|Discovery Channel]]<br />[[DSport]]\n|sat serv 1=[[Tata Sky]]\n|sat chan 1=Channel 155\n|sat serv 2=[[Videocon d2h]]\n|sat chan 2=Channel 111\n|sat serv 3=[[Airtel Digital TV]]\n|sat chan 3=Channel 135 (SD)<br>Channel 136 (HD)\n|sat serv 4=[[Dish TV]]\n|sat chan 4=Channel 126\n|cable serv 1=DEN\n|cable chan 1=Channel 106\n|cable serv 2=[[Hathway]]\n|cable chan 2=Channel 10\n|cable serv 3=GTPL\n|cable chan 3=Channel 8\n|cable serv 4=Fastway\n|cable chan 4=Channel 10\n|cable serv 5=IMCL\n|cable chan 5=Channel 141\n|cable serv 6=BRI Infotainment\n|cable chan 6=Channel 109\n|cable serv 7=BRDS\n|cable chan 7=Channel 108\n|cable serv 8=NXT Digital\n|cable chan 8=Channel 212\n|cable serv 9=SCOD18\n|cable chan 9=Channel 107\n|cable serv 10=7STAR\n|cable chan 10=Channel 6\n|cable serv 11=Homecable\n|cable chan 11=Channel 8\n|cable serv 12=JPR\n|cable chan 12=Channel 108\n|cable serv 13=[[Siti Cable]]\n|cable chan 13=Channel 110/207\n|cable serv 14=A.C.N\n|cable chan 14=Channel 15\n|cable serv 15=Radiant Digitech\n|cable chan 15=Channel 111\n|cable serv 16=ICC Pune\n|cable chan 16=Channel 73\n|cable serv 17=SR Digital\n|cable chan 17=Channel 7\n|cable serv 18=Digiana\n|cable chan 18=Channel 141\n|cable serv 19=Sangli Media Communications\n|cable chan 19=Channel 106\n|cable serv 20=ECN|cable chan 20=Channel 11}}\n\n'''Jeet Prime''' is a Hindi general entertainment channel launched by [[Discovery Networks Asia Pacific]] on 12 February 2018 which airs shows from [[Investigation Discovery (India)|Investigation Discovery]] and [[Scripps Networks Interactive|Scripps]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/companies/people/discovery-expands-vijay-rajput-s-role-to-head-of-dsport-channel-11578558454296.html|title=Discovery expands Vijay Rajput\u2019s role to head of DSPORT channel|first=Lata|last=Jha|date=9 January 2020|website=Livemint}}</ref><ref name=Scrips/> The channel was originally launched as ''Discovery Jeet'' and initially featured original programming.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/television/tv-channels/gecs/not-relying-on-movies-to-garner-jeets-viewership-karan-bajaj-180206|title=Not relying on movies to garner Jeet's viewership: Karan Bajaj|date=2018-02-06|work=Indian Television Dot Com|access-date=2018-02-14|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThis channel replaced [[Investigation Discovery (India)|Investigation Discovery]] on 1 February 2018 and was officially launched on 12 February 2018.<ref name=\":0\" /> The company also shifted their headquarters from Delhi to Mumbai which is more suited for building a national general entertainment channel.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.livemint.com/Companies/p3TPPsBFpoMyl9HhgB1w4M/Karan-Bajaj-A-winning-discovery.html|title=Karan Bajaj: A winning discovery|last=Bansal|first=Shuchi|date=2017-12-22|work=Livemint|access-date=2018-02-14}}</ref> It aims to create 1000 hours of original content a year. The shows will also be available digitally via [[Netflix]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe channel had a reach of 140 million on the day of launch.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.televisionpost.com/jeet-had-a-reach-of-140-million-on-launch-day-claims-discovery/|title=Jeet had a reach of 140 million on launch day, claims Discovery|website=www.televisionpost.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-14}}</ref> Discovery Jeet is also available on Jio TV app and Airtel TV app.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indianable.com/discovery-jeet-channel-number/|title=Watch Discovery Jeet on Jio TV and Airtel TV|website=www.indianable.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-15}}</ref>\n\nDiscovery announced plans to revamp the channel with dubbed content from [[Scripps Networks Interactive|Scripps]] after low ratings.<ref name=Scrips>{{Cite web|url=http://www.afaqs.com/news/story/52900_Discovery-to-dub-foreign-content-as-Hindi-GEC-channel-doesnt-stir-viewers|title=Discovery to dub foreign content as Hindi GEC channel doesn't stir viewers|website=www.afaqs.com|language=en|access-date=2018-05-08}}</ref>\n\n==Programming==\n'''Current'''\n\nAs of October 2018, channel's new programming with Hindi dubbed content from [[Scripps Networks Interactive|Scripps]]\n\n[[Cutthroat Kitchen]]\n\n[[Toddlers & Tiaras|Toddler's and Tiaras]]\n\n[[Guilty Pleasures (TV series)|Guilty Pleasure]]\n\n[[90 Day Fianc\u00e9|90 Days Fianc\u00e9]]\n\n[[Deadly Women]]\n\n===Former===\nAs of June 2018, the channel replaced original programming with Hindi dubbed original shows of the [[Investigation Discovery (India)|Investigation Discovery]] channel.<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n* ''[[A Crime to Remember]]''\n* ''[[Cry Wolfe]]''\n* ''[[Deadly Sins (TV Series)|Deadly Sins]]''\n* ''[[Evil Kin]]''\n* ''[[Murder Among Friends (2016 TV series)|Murder Among Friends]]'' \n* ''[[Unraveled (TV series)|Unraveled]]''\n* ''[[The Perfect Murder (TV series)|The Perfect Murder]]''\n* ''[[Tabloid (TV series)|Tabloid]]''\n* ''[[Web of Lies (TV series)|Web of Lies]]''\n\n===Former original programming===\n*''[[21 Sarfarosh - Saragarhi 1897]]''<ref name=\"DiscvoveryJeet\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.televisionpost.com/discovery-jeet-to-cease-original-programming-by-june-end-launch-fresh-intl-content-in-h2-fy19/|title=Discovery Jeet to cease original programming by June-end, launch fresh intl content in H2 FY19|website=www.televisionpost.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-10}}</ref>\n*''[[Anjaan: Special Crimes Unit]]''<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n*''Comedy High School''<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n*''[[Darr Ke Uss Paar]]''<ref name=DiscvoveryJeet/>\n*''Gabru: Hip Hop Ke Shehzaade''<ref na